narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: All strengths. This class was phenomenal.
Overall I thought everything about the course was perfect. Well done!!

I liked the structure for reading and listening to professors. I would have preferred students sign up to present on certain researchers and also would have preferred that we spend 2 consecutive weeks on each researcher, instead of the broken up schedule we had (i.e. background and contemporary papers one week, followed immediately by discussion of the presentation the next week).

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If you are taking this course it is probably because it is required. Don't worry too much about it, keep an open mind about the strengths of this kind of learning experience, and use Parr as a friendly resource.

100 percent would recommend. It is a phenomenal course both in content and in the experience. It is a great way to lean to critique research while also getting a wide look at what research is currently on the rise and who is working on it.
Yes, especially if you are pursuing the Chemistry B.A major, because it is required!
Yes, a good option for the senior project in Chemistry.
